HEADWORD: Withsay
<hw>With*say"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To contradict; to
gainsay; to deny; to renounce.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Gower.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If that he his Christendom <qex>withsay</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Withset</ent>⟦br⟧
